value.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being fit to be used as a safe means of hydration.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.
A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally anterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally posterior structures.
A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally dorsal structures and missing some or all of what are normally ventral structures.
A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally posterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally anterior structures.
A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some or all of what are normally dorsal structures.

An anteriorized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally anterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally posterior structures.

A dorsalized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally dorsal structures and missing some but not all of what are normally ventral structures.

A posteriorized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally posterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally anterior structures.

A ventralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some but not all of what are normally dorsal structures.

A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally dorso-anterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally ventro-posterior structures.

A dorso-anteriorized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally dorso-anterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally ventro-posterior structures.
A dorso-anteriorized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally dorso-anterior structures.

A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally ventro-posterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally dorso-anterior structures.

A ventro-posteriorized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally ventro-posterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally dorso-anterior structures.
A ventro-posteriorized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally ventro-posterior structures.
An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being abnormally placed or arranged.

definition.value: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of some aspect of that bearer beginning from a position on another entity.

Original label "originates from" changed to current label to differentiate that this term is a positional quality rather than one that connects between an entity and another entity it originates from.

value.value: The ability of a pathogen to produce an infectious disease or disorder in an another organism.
A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered or partially covered with hair that has increased thickness and softness.
An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posteroventrally.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a shape like a crown.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a shape like a shell.

A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an ornamental border consisting of short straight or twisted threads or strips hanging from cut or raveled edges or from a separate band.
A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of a bowl.
Mobility relative to a second entity.

definition.value: For example, distinct anteroposterior mobility of palatine relative to mesethmoid.

value.value: Immobility relative to a second entity.

definition.value: For example: distinct anteroposterior immobility of palatine relative to mesethmoid.

value.value: A shape that is in the form of a plug, being tube-like and expanded on one end.
An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsomedially.
A shape that is in the form of a narrow strip encircling an object.
A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape resembling that of a trough, being narrow, long, and boxlike in shape.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having five angles and five sides.
A growth quality of occurrent in which the growth of an organism, structure or group of organisms is abnormal.
Fibrosis is the formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in an organ or tissue in a reparative or reactive process.

definition.value: Female quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the ovaries and/or uterus from surgical removal.

value.value: The bearer of this quality has_part n=1 of the indicated entity type, where n is bilaterally paired for a comparable organism..

definition.value: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being expanded laterally and or opened outward in shape.

value.value: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed distomedially, ie, pertaining to an inside aspect, but also farther away from the center of the body.
The bearer of this quality has_part n=2 of the indicated entity type, where n is unpaired for a comparable organism.
A structural quality which is held by a bearer where a localized pathological or traumatic structural change, damage, deformity, or discontinuity of tissue, organ, or body part is present.

definition.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by interruptions or gaps.
This term is intended for use for terms such as MP:0010461 discontinuous pulmonary artery and MP:0004157 interrupted aortic arch.

value.value: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's haploid cells undergo chromosome doubling.
An organismal quality of having successfully reproduced.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer being shielded from visible light.

definition.value: Shaded does not refer to radiation more generally, as this would be more shielded than shaded.
A width and length quality which is relatively small, where both width and length are decreased.
A width and length quality that is relatively large, where both width and length are increased.

value.value: A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively high.
A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively low.
A broken quality where an entity is cracked or broken, usually a bone.
